{"title_page": "Haniff Hoosen", "text_new": "{{short description|South African politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Haniff Hoosen\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Parliament of South Africa|MP]]\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| smallimage          = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n| alt                 = \n| caption             =\n| office              = [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (South Africa)|Shadow Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs]] \n| leader              = [[John Steenhuisen]]<br/>[[Mmusi Maimane]]\n| deputy              = [[Cilliers Brink]]\n| term_start          = 5 June 2019\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Kevin Mileham]]\n| successor           = \n| office1             = [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (South Africa)|Shadow Minister of Home Affairs]]\n| leader1             = [[Mmusi Maimane]]\n| deputy1             = [[Archie Figlan]]\n| term_start1         = 5 June 2014\n| term_end1           = 5 June 2019\n| predecessor1        = [[Manuel de Freitas|Manny De Freitas]]\n| successor1          = [[Joe McGluwa]]\n| office2             = Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]]\n| term_start2         = 2007\n| term_end2           = \n| predecessor2        = \n| successor2          =  \n| birthname           = Mohammed Haniff Hoosen\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1972|03|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Chatsworth, KwaZulu-Natal|Chatsworth]], [[Natal Province]], [[South Africa]]\n| death_date          =  \n| death_place         = \n| citizenship         =\n| nationality         = [[South Africa]]n\n| party               = [[Democratic Alliance (South Africa)|Democratic Alliance]]\n| otherparty          = [[Independent Democrats]] {{small|(2005\u20132010)}}<br/>[[New National Party (South Africa)|New National Party]] {{small|(Until 2005)}}\n| spouse              = \n| partner             =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| education           = \n| alma_mater          = \n| occupation          = Member of Parliament\n| profession          = Politician\n| known_for           = \n| committees          = Powers and Privileges of Parliament<br/>Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs\n| portfolio           = \n| awards              =  \n| website             = \n}}\n'''Mohammed Haniff Hoosen''' (born 22 March 1972) is a South African politician who is a Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]] for the [[Democratic Alliance (South Africa)|Democratic Alliance]] (DA). He is the party's shadow minister for Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (2019\u2013present) and was previously shadow minister of Home Affairs (2014\u20132019).<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.da.org.za/2019/06/the-das-new-shadow-cabinet-ready-to-make-parliament-work-for-the-people |title = The DA's new Shadow Cabinet ready to make Parliament work for the people}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.politicsweb.co.za/party/the-das-shadow-cabinet--mmusi-maimane |title = The DA's shadow cabinet - Mmusi Maimane - PARTY &#124; Politicsweb}}</ref>He was the DA's 2016 [[eThekwini Metropolitan Municipality|eThekwini]] mayoral candidate.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/haniff-hoosen-durbans-next-mayor-20160314 | title=Haniff Hoosen: Durban's next mayor?| date=14 March 2016}}</ref> He was a member of the [[Independent Democrats]] from 2005 to 2010 and the party's Secretary-General. He became an MP for the party in 2007 and has served as one since. Hoosen was a member of the Durban municipal council for the New National Party from 1996 to 2001.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://city-press.news24.com/News/da-pins-hopes-on-hoosen-in-ethekwini-20160716 |title = DA pins hopes on Hoosen in eThekwini|date = 17 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/politics/da-candidate-hoosens-np-ties-irk-anc-2049326 |title = DA candidate Hoosen's NP ties irk ANC}}</ref> \n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.parliament.gov.za/person-details/92 Mr Mohammed Haniff Hoosen \u2013 Parliament of South Africa]\n*[https://www.pa.org.za/person/mohammed-haniff-hoosen/ Mr Mohammed Haniff Hoosen \u2013 People's Assembly]\n\n{{Current MPs of South Africa}}\n{{South African Shadow Cabinet}}\n{{SouthAfrica-politician-stub}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hoosen, Haniff}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:South African politicians]]\n[[Category:Democratic Alliance (South Africa) politicians]]\n[[Category:Independent Democrats (South Africa) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Durban]]\n[[Category:People from KwaZulu-Natal]]\n[[Category:South African politicians of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of South Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South African politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Haniff Hoosen\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Parliament of South Africa|MP]]\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| smallimage          = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n| alt                 = \n| caption             =\n| office              = [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (South Africa)|Shadow Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs]] \n| leader              = [[John Steenhuisen]]<br/>[[Mmusi Maimane]]\n| deputy              = [[Cilliers Brink]]\n| term_start          = 5 June 2019\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Kevin Mileham]]\n| successor           = \n| office1             = [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (South Africa)|Shadow Minister of Home Affairs]]\n| leader1             = [[Mmusi Maimane]]\n| deputy1             = [[Archie Figlan]]\n| term_start1         = 5 June 2014\n| term_end1           = 5 June 2019\n| predecessor1        = [[Manuel de Freitas|Manny De Freitas]]\n| successor1          = [[Joe McGluwa]]\n| office2             = Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]]\n| term_start2         = 2007\n| term_end2           = \n| predecessor2        = \n| successor2          =  \n| birthname           = Mohammed Haniff Hoosen\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1972|03|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Chatsworth, KwaZulu-Natal|Chatsworth]], [[Natal Province]], [[South Africa]]\n| death_date          =  \n| death_place         = \n| citizenship         =\n| nationality         = [[South Africa]]n\n| party               = [[Democratic Alliance (South Africa)|Democratic Alliance]]\n| otherparty          = [[Independent Democrats]] {{small|(2005\u20132010)}}<br/>[[New National Party (South Africa)|New National Party]] {{small|(Until 2005)}}\n| spouse              = \n| partner             =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| education           = \n| alma_mater          = \n| occupation          = Member of Parliament\n| profession          = Politician\n| known_for           = \n| committees          = Powers and Privileges of Parliament<br/>Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs\n| portfolio           = \n| awards              =  \n| website             = \n}}\n'''Mohammed Haniff Hoosen''' (born 22 March 1972) is a South African politician who is a Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]] for the [[Democratic Alliance (South Africa)|Democratic Alliance]] (DA). He is the party's shadow minister for Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (2019\u2013present) and was previously shadow minister of Home Affairs (2014\