-single/1383522715|title=Furious \u2013 Single by Jade Bird|website=iTunes|accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| {{non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Uh Huh\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/uh-huh-single/1414685878|title=Uh Huh \u2013 Single by Jade Bird|website=iTunes|accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n| 3\n| \u2014\n| 38\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''Jade Bird''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Love Has All Been Done Before\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/love-has-all-been-done-before-single/1440082243|title=Love Has All Been Done Before- Single by Jade Bird|website=iTunes|accessdate=November 2, 2018}}</ref>\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I Get No Joy\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/jade-bird-new-song-i-get-no-joy-779411/|title=Hear Jade Bird\u2019s Rapid-Fire New Song \u2018I Get No Joy\u2019|publisher=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=15 January 2019|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n|12\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"My Motto\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diymag.com/2019/03/13/jade-bird-new-single-my-motto-listen|title=Jade Bird offers up new single 'My Motto'|publisher=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=13 March 2019|accessdate=3 April 2019}}</ref>\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n| colspan=\"13\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of guest appearances, showing year released, and album name\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Don't Stop\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/dont-stop/1439462110?i=1439462652|title=Vanity Fair by Various Artists|publisher=[[iTunes]] (UK)|accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref>\n| 2018\n| ''Vanity Fair''\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Organization\n! Award\n! Work\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| ANCHOR\n| {{n/a}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Herself}}\n| {{won}}<ref name=\"ANCHOR\" />\n|-\n| [[BBC]]\n| [[Sound of...|Sound of 2018]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{included}}<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/entertainment-arts-42132820/bbc-music-sound-of-2018-the-longlist|title=BBC Music Sound of 2018: The Longlist|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=26 November 2017|accessdate=7 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://listings.ticketweb.co.uk/otw18|title=Ones To Watch 2018|publisher=Ticketweb|accessdate=19 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiox.co.uk/features/x-lists/best-songs-of-2018/|title=Radio X\u2019s Best Songs Of 2018|publisher=[[Radio X (United Kingdom)|Radio X]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=19 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiox.co.uk/new-music/best-new-music-artists-bands-2019/|title=The Best New Music, Artists And Bands For 2019|publisher=[[Radio X (United Kingdom)|Radio X]]|accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Ticketweb\n| Ones To Watch 2018\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Radio X (United Kingdom)|Radio X]]\n| Best Songs Of 2018\n| \"Love Has All Been Done Before\"\n|-\n| Great X-Pectations 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Herself}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2019\n| [[MTV]] Push\n| Ones To Watch 2019\n| {{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/mtv-push-ones-to-watch-2019/news/voting-for-mtv-push-ones-to-watch-2019-is-open|title=voting for mtv push: ones to watch 2019 is open!|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Radio X\n| Best of British 2019\n| \"Uh-Huh\"\n| {{nom|#84}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://charts.radiox.co.uk/2019/|title=Best of British 2019|publisher=Radio X|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Americana Music Honors & Awards]]\n| Emerging Act of the Year\n| {{n/a|Herself}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{nom}}<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://americanamusic.org/news/americana-announces-its-2019-honors-awards-nominees|title=Americana announces its 2019 honors & awards nominees|publisher=[[Americana Music Honors & Awards]]|date=14 May 2019|accessdate=1 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://completemusicupdate.com/article/aim-announces-2019-independent-music-awards-nominees/|title=AIM announces 2019 Independent Music Awards nominees|publisher=[[Association of Independent Music]]|date=24 July 2019|accessdate=1 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[Association of Independent Music|AIM Independent Music Awards]]\n| Best Independent Album\n| ''Jade Bird''\n|-\n| UK Independent Breakthrough \n| rowspan=5 {{n/a|Herself}}\n|-\n| International Breakthrough\n| {{won}}<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8529026/aim-independent-music-awards-winners-list</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2020\n|[[Gaffa (magazine)|Denmark GAFFA Awards]]\n| Best Foreign New Artist\n| {{pending}}<ref>https://gaffa.dk/prisen/afstemningen</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[NME Awards]]\n| Best New Act in the World\n| rowspan=2 {{nom}}<ref>https://www.nme.com/awards/winners</ref>\n|-\n| Best British New Act\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Jade Bird (musician)|Jade Bird}}\n*[http://www.jade-bird.com Official website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bird, Jade}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century English singers]]\n[[Category:British singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Military brats]]\n[[Category:People from Northumberland]]\n[[Category:21st-century English women singers]]\n[[Category:Bibliophiles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Jade Bird\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Jade Bird 09 07 2018 -17 (43969330274).jpg\n| caption          = Bird in 2018\n| birth_name       = Jade Elizabeth Bird\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1997|10|01}}<ref name=\"Princeton\">{{cite web |title= Jade Bird is a Rising Star {{!}} Princeton Tonight Interview |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hg0fyGYTYO0|website=YouTube|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Hexham]], [[Northumberland]], England\n| origin           = [[Croydon]], [[South London]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Americana (music)|Americana]]\n* [[Indie (music)|indie]]\n* [[Folk music|folk]]\n* [[rock music|rock]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*songwriter\n*musician\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar \n* piano\n}}\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = [[Glassnote Records|Glassnote]]\n| website          = {{URL|jade-bird.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Jade Elizabeth Bird'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/Catalog.aspx?detail=writerid&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&keyid=1782673&subid=0|title=Songwriter/Composer: Bird, Jade Elizabeth|work=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]] |accessdate=24 January 2018}}</ref> (born 1 October 1997)<ref name=\"Broadway\">{{cite web|title=Jade Bird Something American EP Out Today on Glassnote Records|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Jade-Bird-Something-American-EP-Out-Today-on-Glassnote-Records-20170707|website=Broadway World|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref> is an English singer, songwriter, musician and former Stage School pupil. Her debut [[Extended play|EP]], ''Something American'', was released in July 2017. ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' described her vocals as \"raw and robust\" with [[Tony Visconti]] stating \"she sings so adroitly, she's very intelligent as a singer and there's nothing she can't do\".<ref name=\"RS\" /><ref name=\"ANCHOR\">{{Citation|last=ANCHOR Award|title=ANCHOR 2017 winner portrait - JADE BIRD|date=2017-10-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7eD0qEB2mJU|access-date=2018-10-22}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nJade Bird was born in Hexham, Northumberland, where she lived until she was two.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hexham-born singer is one to watch|url=https://www.hexham-courant.co.uk/features/17256296.hexham-born-singer-is-one-to-watch/|website=www.hexham-courant.co.uk|accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref> Bird and her family moved to London when she was two years old, and lived on a military base in Germany when she was five. She later moved to [[Bridgend]], [[South Wales]], where she attended Bryntirion Comprehensive School. At age 16, began attending the [[BRIT School]] in [[Croydon]], which she graduated from in 2016. While at the BRIT School, she performed at gigs several times a week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jade Bird interview: I gigged five times a week while doing my A-levels|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/music/jade-bird-interview-i-gigged-five-times-a-week-while-doing-my-alevels-a3832981.html|website=standard.co.uk|accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web|title=See U.K. country music breakout Jade Bird cover 'Grinnin' In Your Face'|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/10/04/jade-bird-grinnin-your-face-cover/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref> During her Piano Session with [[Huw Stephens]] on [[BBC Radio 1]] in October 2017, she noted that she had travelled around as a child due to being in an Army family. She lived in South Wales, [[Chesterfield]] and [[M\u00f6nchengladbach]], Germany, which had a big influence on her music.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jade Bird Piano Session|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09b1glr|website=[[BBC Radio]]|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2017, after leaving Stage School, she was sent to tour the United States with [[Brent Cobb]].<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/country/lists/10-new-country-artists-you-need-to-know-july-2017-w491510/jade-bird-w491518|title=10 New Country Artists You Need to Know: July 2017|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref> She played a showcase event at [[South by Southwest]] in [[Austin, Texas]] in March 2017 and later in the year she opened for [[First Aid Kit (band)|First Aid Kit]], [[Son Little]] and [[London Grammar]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SXSW Schedule 2017: Jade Bird|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2017/events/MS39578|website=[[South by South West]]|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"EW\"/> Bird's band consists of [[Mystery Jets|Will Rees]] on guitar, [[Matt Johnson (drummer)|Matt Johnson]] on drums and bassist Linus Fenton. In 2017, Bird won the ANCHOR 2017 award of the ''Reeperbahn Festival'' in [[Hamburg]].<ref name=\"ANCHOR\" /> She was also a finalist for the [[BBC Sound Of]] award in 2018. Her debut [[Extended play|EP]], ''Something American'', was recorded in the [[Catskill Mountains]] in [[Palenville]] and [[Woodstock, New York|Woodstock]] in upstate New York.<ref>{{cite web|title=BBC Music Sound Of 2018: Jade Bird|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/4lkK7sGpmQTMXylT2tr7xHC/jade-bird|website=BBC.co.uk|accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn April 19, 2019, she released her [[Jade Bird (album)|self-titled debut album]].\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"7\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/54376/jade-bird/|title=Jade Bird {{!}} full Official Chart history|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Independent Singles and Albums Charts|UK<br>Indie]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/independent-albums-chart/20190426/131/|title=Official Independent Albums Chart Top 50: 26 April 2019|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Independent Singles and Albums Charts|UK<br>Folk]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/americana-albums-chart/20190426/americana/|title=Official Americana Albums Chart Top 40: 26 April 2019|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Scottish Singles and Albums Charts|SCO]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-albums-chart/20190426|title=Official Scottish Albums Chart \u2013 26 April 2019|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Jade+Bird|title=Discographie Jade Bird|publisher=[[Swiss Hitparade]]|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard charts|US<br>Folk]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/americana-folk-albums/2019-05-04|title=Americana/Folk Albums \u2014 May 4, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Heatseekers Albums|US<br>Heat.]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/heatseekers-albums/2019-05-04|title=Heatseekers Albums \u2014 May 4, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Jade Bird (album)|Jade Bird]]''\n|\n* Released: 19 April 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/jade-bird/1446920412|title=Jade Bird by Jade Bird|publisher=[[iTunes]] (UK)|accessdate=4 January 2019}}</ref>\n* Label: [[Glassnote Records]]\n* Format: Digital download, CD, vinyl\n| 10 || 2 || 1 || 10 || 91 || 14 || 1\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope